tjceu.quest.db.122.title=Item Placeholder
tjceu.quest.db.122.desc=Nuclear waste, a byproduct of all nuclear processing, is a poor source of nearly every element on the periodic table. The vast majority of metals, along with a non-insignificant amount of radon, xenon, and krypton, can be sourced here. Make sure you build your nuclear reprocessing sufficiantly well, as it will be functioning for the forseeable future.
