tjceu.quest.db.440.title=More Than Meets The Eye
tjceu.quest.db.440.desc=One generator per machine gets pretty annoying, and it can be hard to generate your first MV amp when you're working with LV components and infrastructure. Luckily, Greg has a solution to this: transformers. An MV transformer (crafted from LV parts) will take 4 amps of LV and output 1 amp of MV, or intake 1 amp of MV and output 4 amps of LV. Transformers can be used in chains to power 16 machines with one generator. %n%nIn addition, energynet has some broken mechanics. Energy limits are calculated based on input, so you can have 50 generators on a 1amp line, and 50 machines drawing one amp each. As long as you never input more than the amperage of the cables from 1 individual source, you can abuse this mechanic to make lines of machines that share their energy sources, vastly reducing the total amount of generators you need.
