tjceu.quest.db.482.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.483.title=§c256k§r ME Fluid Storage Component
tjceu.quest.db.483.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.484.title=Block of Tungstencarbide
tjceu.quest.db.484.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.485.title=Warp Core
tjceu.quest.db.485.desc=In order to journey to other planets you will need to make a warp core. This needs to be built on a space station. In order to fly down from the space station to a planet you will need your rocket. %n%nMake set a home on each planet so you can travel between them with ease.%n%nFor more guidance building and opperating the warp core, please visit the TJ discord or the AR wiki (though this is famously incomprehensible).
tjceu.quest.db.486.title=Coal Ore
tjceu.quest.db.486.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.487.title=Bastnasite Ore
tjceu.quest.db.487.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.488.title=Celestial Crystals
tjceu.quest.db.488.desc=In order to make celestial crystals you need to throw a rock crystal and stardust into a pool of starlight. Later one you can use a machine to get a tier one crystal cluster. The machine recipe can also be used to reroll already made celestial crystals.%n%n§4The machine recipe will also accept attuned crystals, so make sure you're using the right one.%n%n§fGrowing a crystal on top of starmetal ore can speed up growth. This does have the chance to return the ore back to iron however so it is best to keep a collector crystal linked to it
tjceu.quest.db.489.title=Enriched Naquadric Compound Ore
tjceu.quest.db.489.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.490.title=Luminous Crafting Table
tjceu.quest.db.490.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.491.title=Titan dim ID 400
tjceu.quest.db.491.desc=To get a decent amount of oil and graphite  you will need to warp to the carbon wasteland. This planet requires an artifact, the charcoal log.
tjceu.quest.db.492.title=End Uranium Ore
tjceu.quest.db.492.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.493.title=Linking Tool
tjceu.quest.db.493.desc=Linking tools are used to link collector crystals to blocks. By using this to connect a collector crystal to iron ore it will slowly transform into starmetal ore. It is important for the deep dark portal, where starmetal can be mined instead.
tjceu.quest.db.494.title=Plutonium Ore
tjceu.quest.db.494.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.495.title=Resonating Wand
tjceu.quest.db.495.desc=Resonating wands used to start crafts for many astral tables. There are also rumors that if a wand is held in your off hand at night on Pluto important places to dig may reveal themself
tjceu.quest.db.496.title=Phobos dim ID 402
tjceu.quest.db.496.desc=As you progress you will find that there is never enough chlorine and fluoride. The moon of mars Phobos takes care of both, you will need a block of salt to warp, and will find it is rich in salt, fluorite, and lepidolite. In addition you can use the fluid plants to collect up pure chlorine and fluoride.
tjceu.quest.db.497.title=Platinum Metallic Powder Ore
tjceu.quest.db.497.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.498.title=Neptunium Ore
tjceu.quest.db.498.desc=These ores can be used to suppliment Pu and Np production for nuclear, which you will need as you scale into using a lot of Pu for %nquantum circuits & beyond.
tjceu.quest.db.499.title=Space Station Assembler
tjceu.quest.db.499.desc=To launch a space station, you must first package the space station into a satelite bay using the space station assembler, which functions in a similar manner to the rocket assembling machine. You must also provide a fresh station ID chip when building your satelite. %n%nOnce you have the space station container, place it inside a satelite bay on a rocket, and place the newly made station ID chip into the rocket's guidance computer. %n%nGet on the rocket, and launch. This should bring you and the space station to space, deploy the space station, and land on it.%n%nLike so many other AR mechanics, this is confusing and poorly documented. For additional help, as with everything, ask on the TJ discord.
tjceu.quest.db.500.title=End Scheelite Ore
tjceu.quest.db.500.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.501.title=Dilithium
tjceu.quest.db.501.desc=The moon has Dilithium ore. The GT prospector can't see it, and neither can the GT miners. This is because dilithium ore is added by Vulpes, and means that you will have to do a small amount of lunar mining by hand. However, with proper management you can visit every warp destination using less than a stack of Dilithium in total. %n%nThis vein also contains rutile ore, useful for making titanium in a more efficent way than bauxite electrolysis. Of course, this vein contains bauxite as well. Later on, you may consider setting up the Red Mud processing line to maximize your titanium production.
tjceu.quest.db.502.title=Collector crystal
tjceu.quest.db.502.desc=Collector crystals can be found in monuments usually in the room under the fountain. If a crafting table is placed near the crystal it will automatically provide the table with starlight. These crystal will also be necessary for making star metal ore
tjceu.quest.db.503.title=If you do not want to use advanced rocketry
tjceu.quest.db.503.desc=If you do not want to play using advanced rocketry. Fret not, here are repeatable quests you can use to teleport to these planets. In order to have access to these you will be required to hand in your warp core and items needed to make a space station. For each planet you must present the required artafact. Then there will be a small fee of rocket fuel and dilithium. %n%n§4Due to the nature of these commands it is HIGHLY recommended you have charged ender IO boots to negate fall damage. You will spawn in at 256 256 256
tjceu.quest.db.504.title=Mercury
tjceu.quest.db.504.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.505.title=Charcoal Log
tjceu.quest.db.505.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.506.title=Aquamarine Ore
tjceu.quest.db.506.desc=Aquamarine and starmetal veins spawn in the deep dark, though if you're using starlight rocket fuel for power it is strongly recommended to setup a collector crystal for more consistent automation. The GT miner and scanner will also not see starmetal, meaning if you want to collect it you will have to manually mine it (gross).
tjceu.quest.db.507.title=Magic Feather
tjceu.quest.db.507.desc=Base range is 200 blocks. Each tier adds 50 block range
tjceu.quest.db.508.title=Enriched Naquadah Ore
tjceu.quest.db.508.desc=
tjceu.quest.db.509.title=For the love of god
tjceu.quest.db.509.desc=For the love of god please don't pump up the oceans on planets. They are purely cosmetic. You will ruin your game via fluid calculations as Minecraft struggles to handle the mess of flowing blocks. All fluids offered in the oceans are in the fluid drilling multiblocks.
