tjceu.quest.db.941.title=Some Notes on Power Generation:
tjceu.quest.db.941.desc=Biodiesel is best made using the most advanced vairent of canola -- it's simply more diesel per unit time.%n%nThe 'green goo' rocket fuel is strong and availible early, and is completely renewable. Starlight rocket fuel is an enourmous upgrade, but a significant amount of infrastructure to pull off. %n%nThe large naq reactor has been buffed considerably, and boosting it with oxygen plasma is a good idea.%n%nPlasma turbine rotors barely take durability damage.%n%nYou can use hot coolant for a significant amount of power, either from the heat exchanger (slow and not recommended) or from advanced fusion (supercritical steam, you will probably have to void excess).
