tjceu.quest.db.947.title=Automatic Maintenance Hatch
tjceu.quest.db.947.desc=To overcome some weirdness with maintenance and large machines, a few require auto-maintenance hatches to function. As you cannot make these for (likely) another tier, you'll need a way to run your LRE's. Luckily for you, we made this here quest! Give us 8 auto-taping hatches and you'll get 4 full-auto ones in return. This isn't repeatable, so be sure to ration your fancy new full-auto maintenance hatches wisely.
tjceu.quest.db.948.title=Large Rocket Engine (LRE)
tjceu.quest.db.948.desc=The Large Rocket Engine works like the DE and EDE, except it generates LuV power (and consumes rocket fuels instead of combustables). It consumes %nliquid oxygen to boost, as well as an insane 37500mb of air per second. When boosted, this monster is capable of outputting 12 amps of LuV, enough power to be viable well into the midgame.
tjceu.quest.db.949.title=Methanol or Ethanol?
tjceu.quest.db.949.desc=If you elect to use biodiesel, you'll see that there are two ways to produce it. %n%nMethanol is better in terms of EU in to biodiesel produced, as well as fully passive from carbon, oxygen, and hydrogen, but Ethanol may be easier in the beginning due to the fact that a) you need to set Ethanol up for Polyethylene regardless, and b) the relatively small infrastructure requirement it represents.
